class Solution {
    public int minChanges(int n, int k) {
        if ((n | k) != n) return -1;
        return Integer.bitCount(n ^ k);
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution checks if it's possible to make n equal to k by verifying if all bits set in k are also set in n. It then counts the number of bits that need to be changed by XORing n and k and counting the number of bits set in the result.
